===message:I agree with you about the brainwashing, it was done on both sides.  The Soviets and the Americans used propaganda in many ways to have their citizens think poorly against the other country, the soviets mainly in films.  I agree also that it was because of fear.  It was the communist east against the capitalist west.  Both countries feared that one would become more powerful than the other.  The U.S. wanted to link all other economies to their own to become an international giant and wanted the soviets to join.  When the soviets wanted no part of the U.S. economy one key way for the U.S. to threaten the soviets was to taunt them with nuclear power, however, the soviets were able to even up the nuclear race by exploding their own hydrogen bomb months later.
