===message:I would like to touch on Wendy's post by saying that I cannot say that I believe that each side was motivated "primarily" by fear.  It could be better described as distrust of the other's motives.  This distrust then started a series of defensive tactics to head off agression from the other side which was perceived as a threat by the opposition.  This notion of a threat posed by each side set off the propaganda war which multiplied the conflict. 
